2 WHEREAS, she currently works for the St. Tammany Parish Clerk of Court finance
3 department; and
4 WHEREAS, during Madison's one-year tenure with the St. Tammany Parish Fair,
5 she will serve as the spokesperson and representative for the fair, making specials
6 appearances and performing philanthropic work; and
7 WHEREAS, in January 2026, as Queen, Madison competed at the Louisiana
8 Association of Fairs and Festivals for the title of LAFF Queen, representing the St.
9 Tammany Parish Fair and placing in the top ten in a competition with over sixty fair and
10 festival queens.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
12 does hereby commend Madison Hogan on being crowned the 100th Miss St. Tammany
13 Parish Fair Queen.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
15 Madison Hogan.
